  "description": "Hadar Erik Berglund was a Swedish professor and rector at the University of Gothenburg. He was born in Stockholm in 1891 to postman E. Wilhelm Berglund and Kristina Olsson. He married Emma Petersson in 1918 and had two children: Eskil and Ann-Mari. Berglund earned his law degree from Uppsala University in 1913 and later became a docent of Procedural Law at Uppsala. He held several other academic positions before becoming a professor at the University of Gothenburg, where he also served as rector. He is the author of several works in the field of law and was honored with the Royal Norwegian Order of St. Olav, Danish Order of the Dannebrog, and the Finnish Order of the White Rose." 
